description.plain:
Dominic David Fike (born December 30, 1995), mononymously known as Dominic Fike (previously L$G or Dom), is an American singer-songwriter, rapper and producer hailing from Naples, Florida.

Fike was raised by a single mother and grew up with a younger brother, Alex, a sister, Apollonia, or “Apple”—who inspired the apple tattoo beneath his right eye—and an older brother, Sean. Dominic started playing guitar at ten, citing pop-punk and rock bands like ​​blink-182, Red Hot Chili Peppers and Weezer as inspirations.

In the early stages of Fike’s music career, he was part of the Southwest Florida-based rap collective Backhouse and rap group ​lameboyzent, the initials (LBE) of which are tattooed on his forehead. He sings about this period of his life in “Westcoast Collective.”

Following his arrest in 2017 for alleged assault of a police officer, Fike released a rough draft of his Don’t Forget About Me, Demos EP. Upon release, Dominic Fike reportedly signed a $4 million record contract with Columbia Records and officially released Don’t Forget About Me, Demos on October 16, 2018.

In 2019, he gained a surge of new fans as boyband BROCKHAMPTON’s leader Kevin Abstract, directed an alternative music video for his song “3 Nights,” titled “This Is Dominic Fike.” He was later featured on two tracks on Abstract’s 2019 album ARIZONA BABY.

songs.title: 3 Nights

description.plain:
“3 Nights” is the first song off of Dominic Fike’s 2018 EP Don’t Forget About Me, Demos. It is one of two songs on the EP that Fike didn’t write and produce himself, the other being “Socks.”

“3 Nights” seems to be about the progression of a relationship going from the narrator not being 100% interested, to falling in love, to then reluctantly drifting apart.

On April 4, 2019, Fike released an official music video for the track. Known boyband BROCKHAMPTON released an alternate music video called ‘'This is Dominic Fike," starring the man himself.

songs.title: Chicken Tenders

description.plain:
“Chicken Tenders” is the first single from Dominic Fike’s debut full-length, What Could Possibly Go Wrong. On the song, he fuses his typical alternative pop sound with R&B, singing about living in luxury with his lover. The track also features an infectious chorus with high-pitched vocals about having chicken tenders with the lover.

Originally scheduled to drop on June 5, 2020, Dom pushed the track’s release forward three weeks due to the ongoing George Floyd protests. In an Instagram post, the Florida singer explained:

Last week, I was supposed to put out the first song from my debut album. Instead something much more important happened. People were forced to have a conversation that’s been long overdue. It doesn’t feel right to release music today but it does feel right to continue this conversation.

Dominic first performed the song live during a September 2019 Chicago show, and later confirmed the title in January 2020, along with the rest of the album’s tracklist. He revealed the artwork and release date in a tweet on June 22, 2020.

songs.title: Açaí Bowl

description.plain:
“Açaí Bowl” was first premiered by Dominic Fike at his hometown show in Naples, Florida on December 21st, 2018. The track was also played at Dominic’s Hammer Museum show in Los Angeles, on April 19th, 2019.

Açaí is a Brazilian dish made of frozen and mashed açaí palm fruit. It is served as a smoothie in a bowl or glass, and is commonly topped with a lot of things, like granola, banana, chocolate, powdered milk, condensed milk etc.

The artwork shows a napkin with a bowl/cup stain and the song title, written in the smoothie form of açai palm fruit.
